Articles.Content:
I have done update to 0.90 through the launcher on two computers, and both times I get an error message in the update log saying:

rsync: rename "/cygdrive/c/Games/Kerbal Space Program/Launcher_Data/.output_log.txt.GKs826" -> "Launcher_Data/output_log.txt": Device or resource busy (16)

Apart from that the game seems just fine. Do I need to do something about this? Can I redo the update somehow?

Edited December 20, 2014 by Peek

No, that's fine. The output_log.txt files are merely debug logs, and strictly speaking simply shouldn't be included in an update. Looks like someone at Squad just forgot to delete the file on the servers after running some tests or something.

Nothing to worry about.
Great, had a feeling it was something like that. Thanks for the reply!
I'm experiencing this exact problem, but the patcher stops at 93%/100% and when I hit OK then play to launcj the game, it gets stuck on the blank loading screen :/

@ThePuffinPunk this thread is almost a year and a half old, and is talking about a different version of KSP. 

The launcher/patcher for updating the game has been broken for some time. Instead of using that to update, go to wherever you bought the game and download the latest version's zip file.
